@page "/components/HxSpinner"

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxSpinner)">
    <DocHeading Title="Border spinner" />
    <p>Use the border spinners for a lightweight loading indicator.</p>
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_Border)" Tabs="false" />

    <DocHeading Title="Colors" />
    <p>You can customize the color of the spinner with the <code>Color</code> parameter.</p>
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_Colors)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Growing spinner" />
    <p>If you don't prefer a border spinner, switch to the grow spinner. While it doesn't technically spin, it does repeatedly grow!</p>
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_Growing)" Tabs="false" />

    <p>Once again, you can customize the color of the spinner with the <code>Color</code> parameter.</p>
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_GrowingColors)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Size" />
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_Size)" Tabs="false" />

    <DocHeading Title="Alignment" />
    <p>Use <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/utilities/flex/">flex</a> and <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/5.3/utilities/text/">text</a> utilities (through the surrounding markup) to position spinners exactly where you need them.</p>
    <Demo Type="typeof(HxSpinner_Demo_Alignment)" Tabs="false" />

    <DocHeading Title="Buttons" />
    <p>To indicate a busy action on a button, use the built-in <a href="/components/HxButton#spinner-and-single-click-protection"><code>Spinner</code></a> support of <code>HxButton</code> rather than placing a spinner manually.</p>
</ApiDoc>
